%% Fig 4.12 — Sequence: login & JWT issuance (P1)
%% Source: author, derived from auth/AuthController, AuthService, security/* (ARCHITECTURE.md §5)
sequenceDiagram
    actor U as User
    participant FE as Next.js (web)
    participant AC as AuthController
    participant AS as AuthService
    participant TP as JwtTokenProvider
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    U->>FE: enter email + password
    FE->>AC: POST /api/auth/login
    AC->>AS: authenticate(email, password)
    AS->>DB: find active user by email
    DB-->>AS: user (password_hash, role)
    AS->>AS: BCrypt.matches(raw, hash)
    alt invalid credentials
        AS-->>AC: AUTH_INVALID_CREDENTIALS
        AC-->>FE: 401 ApiResponse(error)
    else valid
        AS->>TP: generate(sub=id, role, exp) — HS256
        TP-->>AS: access JWT
        AS->>DB: persist hashed refresh token
        AS-->>AC: {token, refreshToken, user}
        AC-->>FE: 200 ApiResponse + httpOnly cookie
        FE->>FE: redirect by role (student/teacher/admin)
    end
